    "comment": "Rationale: Fig.2: \"Cbln1 and the NTD of GluD2 cooperatively induce synaptogenesis in vitro and in vivo\"\nPresynapse formation onto GluD2 expressing HEK cells is perturbed in Cbln1 KO neurons. Effect is absent when truncated versions of GluD2 are used. Synapse formation is restored in Cbln1 KO mice after injection of HA-Cbln1 in WT animals, but not in GluD2 KO animals.. Experimental description: 20/11/2017 Pim\n- Overexpressed protein is of rat species: \"Rat cDNAs encoding GluD1, GluD2 and GluK2 were gifts from Dr. J. Boulter \"\n- Cell culures were of mouse species: \"Mixed cerebellar cultures were prepared from embryonic day 17 to day-of-birth ICR, GluD2-null (ho5J) or cbln1-null mice \"\n- Rat species was selected based on speceis of overexpressed protein. Mouse annotation can also be made.",
